{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"text":"The test for `restartAiCli` fails because `interruptAiCli` uses `processInfo.childProcess.kill()` — and the process likely dies and clears before `interruptAiCli` can mark it interrupted. Let me look at the issue. The problem is that `interruptAiCli` reads from `sessionStore.getActiveProcess()` which checks the sessionStore entry. But since this is a standalone `sleep` process (not spawned by `executeAiCli`), the `close` event handler that calls `clearActiveProcess` is never set up. So `interruptAiCli` should work. The issue might be that `restartAiCli` checks `isAiCliRunning` after kill. Since there's no `close` event handler to clear the process, it stays in the store. Let me re-examine the flow.\n\nThe `sleep` process's `close` event never fires a handler that would call `sessionStore.clearActiveProcess`. So `isAiCliRunning` will keep returning true, and the poll loop will time out at 10s.\n\nI need to listen for the child close event and clear the process. Let me fix the test:","type":"text"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZKqV8qGuZd4vxEugWqpr","model":"claude-opus-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":701,"output_tokens":1,"cache_read_input_tokens":70768},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e2c5d48-2c5c-4924-9a4c-071d0c254490","uuid":"a7d711fe-b378-41f7-b800-310f44ba6cb9"}
