sage through AI CLI\n- createSessionBindService({bindingsPath}): SessionBindingService — F-018 factory with deferred init\n- SessionBindingService.bindSession(webId, chatId): {ok} — bind web session to Telegram chat\n- SessionBindingService.getBoundChatId(webId): string|null — lookup binding\n- SessionBindingService.getBoundWebSessions(chatId): string[] — reverse lookup\n- SessionBindingService.ensureReady(): Promise<void> — wait for deferred init\n- sessionStore.append(key, role, content) — append message to session\n- sessionStore.toPrompt(key, channel): string — build prompt with context\n- realtimeHub.subscribe(key, listener): unsubscribe — SSE event pub/sub\n- realtimeHub.publish(key, event) — broadcast event to subscribers\n- chatWithSession({channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks}): Promise<reply> — legacy Web chat (deprecated by F-018)\n- createOutputHistoryService(maxEntries?): {addOutput, getHistory, clearHistory} — F-020 per-session output ring buffer\n- profileStore.init({persistencePath?}): Promise<void> — F-021 load profiles from disk (accepts path override)\n- profileStore.addProfile(profile): Promise<Profile> — F-021 add/update profile, persists to disk\n- profileStore.removeProfile(name): Promise<void> — F-021 remove profile (throws if default protected name)\n- profileStore.listProfiles(): Profile[] — F-021 all profiles\n- profileStore.hasProfile(name): boolean — F-021 existence check\n- backendRegistry.updateBackend(name, fields): void — F-021 update permissionFlag/timeoutMs on existing backend\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: node:child_process: spawn for AI CLI process\n- uses: zod: config validation\n- uses: node:fs/promises: session persistence, bindings file, profile file\n- imports: src/config.js: runtime configuration\n- imports: src/security/guard.js: sanitizeInput\nKEY_FILES:\n- ai-cli-service.js: AI CLI executor with heartbeat, timeout, metrics, restart (612 lines)\n- message-router.js: F-018 unified message processor (128 lines)\n- session-bind.js: F-018 session binding with persistence (~220 lines)\n- session-store.js: in-memory session state (427 lines)\n- realtime-hub.js: SSE event pub/sub (35 lines)\n- chat-service.js: legacy chat via codebuddy adapter (80 lines, deprecated)\n- config-service.js: F-017 runtime config manager — hot-reload via process.env, safe key whitelist, sensitive masking (337 lines)\n- output-history-service.js: F-020 per-session output ring buffer factory (~80 lines)\n- profile-store.js: F-021 profile CRUD + JSON persistence (~160 lines)\n- backend-registry.js: F-015/F-021 backend registry with permissionFlag/timeoutMs support (~230 lines)\nSUBDIRS:\n- src/services/output-history-service.prizm -> L2 detail for output history\nTRAPS:\n- SessionBindingService uses deferred init — always call ensureReady() before sync methods in async contexts\n- SessionBindingService persistence is fire-and-forget — tests must call flush() to verify file writes\n- messageRouter does not expose heartbeat hooks — Telegram heartbeat progress disabled after F-018 migration\n- Runtime bindings created via POST /api/bind do NOT auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push (F-018 gap)\n- config-service originalEnvValues captured at module init; if env vars set after import, use setConfig first (which lazy-captures original) before reset | FIX: ensure env vars are set before module import in tests, or setConfig will lazy-capture the pre-modification value\n- output-history-service singleton lives in output.js — tests must inject mock via handlerCtx.outputHistoryService to avoid mutating shared singleton state\n- profileStore singleton must be init()d at startup with {persistencePath} — tests must create isolated ProfileStore instances, not the singleton\n- backendRegistry.registerBackend() throws if name already registered — wrap in try/catch at startup when re-registering profiles after restart | FIX: check getBackend() before registerBackend() or catch the throw\n- ai-cli-service reads sessionBackend.permissionFlag and sessionBackend.timeoutMs at execution time — these fields must be set at registerBackend() time or via updateBackend() for profile switching to fully apply\n- restartAiCli polls isAiCliRunning (100ms intervals, 10s max) before spawning new process — the old process close handler must call clearActiveProcess for polling to succeed | FIX: tests must register a child.on('close') handler that calls clearActiveProcess\nUPDATED: 2026-03-23\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":49,"oldLines":8,"newStart":49,"newLines":8,"lines":[" - SessionBindingService persistence is fire-and-forget — tests must call flush() to verify file writes"," - messageRouter does not expose heartbeat hooks — Telegram heartbeat progress disabled after F-018 migration"," - Runtime bindings created via POST /api/bind do NOT auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push (F-018 gap)","-- config-service originalEnvValues captured at module init; if env vars set after import, use setConfig first (which lazy-captures original) before reset | FIX: ensure env vars are set before module import in tests, or setConfig will lazy-capture the pre-modification value","-- output-history-service singleton lives in output.js — tests must inject mock via handlerCtx.outputHistoryService to avoid mutating shared singleton state","+- config-service originalEnvValues lazy-captured at first setConfig call | FIX: set env vars before import or call setConfig before reset","+- output-history-service singleton in output.js — tests inject mock via handlerCtx to avoid shared state mutation"," - profileStore singleton must be init()d at startup with {persistencePath} — tests must create isolated ProfileStore instances, not the singleton"," - backendRegistry.registerBackend() throws if name already registered — wrap in try/catch at startup when re-registering profiles after restart | FIX: check getBackend() before registerBackend() or catch the throw"," - ai-cli-service reads sessionBackend.permissionFlag and sessionBackend.timeoutMs at execution time — these fields must be set at registerBackend() time or via updateBackend() for profile switching to fully apply"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
